Description: Fragment of lower wall and foot of black-glazed pottery cup or bowl; fine pale brown clay; wholly black- glazed, misfired reddish in parts; graffito on underside.
Curator's comments: The clay is rather light for Attic.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 376)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GS.112)
